material design website. (material.io) (Documentation )

(Material Design Subject):
Button, Floating Action, Material Card CheckBox, Snackbar, Top App bar, Bottom app bar, tabs layout.


# How to use Material Component:
	1: add material design library.
		(mavle-repo)
		(add dependencies)
	2: Theme:
		1: change theme (Material Component)
	3: in XML:
		1: Now can use material component
(if you add another element into your layout file, for example the checkBox. by default the checkbox from the material library will be use )


1# Button (Material)
	2: backgroundTint
	3: style
@style/Widget.MaterialComponents.Button.UnelevatedButton

@style/Widget.MaterialComponent.Button.OutlinedButton

@style/Widget.MaterialComponent.Button.TextButton




(Elements only came from material library)

1# floating action button

<com.google.android.material.floatingactionbutton.FloatingActionButton

	Position
	* align Parent Bottom
	* align Parent End
	* margin End
	* margin bottom

	* src (icon)
	* android: backgroundTint (background color)
	* app: backgroundTint (border color)
	* app: rippleColor (color change while click)

	*setOnClickListener

	usees: floating action button + bottom app bar navigation.


2# Snackbar
	1: (add) id (xml parent layout)

	2: snackbarID.make( parentLayout, text, INDEFINITE/SHORT/LONG)
	3: .setAction( text , new View.onClickListener)
	4: .show();

	.make has 3 input ==
	1: (the layout we are going to show snackbar)
	2: (text)
	3: (LENGTH_INDEFINITE)

	.setAction(Text, click)  [snackbar button]
	.show

	color:
		.setActionTextColor()
		.setTextColor()
	1: getColor(R.color.colorName)
	2: getResources().getColor(R.color.colorName)
	3: Color.RED (android.graphics) [if you dont have the RED color in your resources you can get color from this class.]



3# CardView
<com.google.android.material.card.MaterialCardView


